creg_cgreg.units: lower nibble of first byte (creg)/upper nibble of first byte (cgreg) : 0 = not registered, is not currently searching a new operator to register to; 1 = registered, home network; 2 = not registered, but currently searching a new operator to register to; 3 = registration denied; 4 = unknown; 5 = registered, roaming

cereg.units: 0 = not registered, is not currently searching a new operator to register to; 1 = registered, home network; 2 = not registered, but currently searching a new operator to register to; 3 = registration denied; 4 = unknown; 5 = registered, roaming

rssi.units: received signal strength indicator : 0 = -113dBm or less; 1 = -111dBm; 2 through 30 = -109dBm through -53dBm; 31 = -51dBm or greater; 99 = Not known or not detectable; 100 = -116dBm or less; 101 = -115dBm; 102 through 190 = -114dBm through -26dBm; 191 = -25dBm or greater; 199 = Not known or not detectable; 100~199 = Extended to be used in TD-SCDMA indicating received signal code power (RSCP)

overall_access_technology.units: 0 = GSM; 2 = UTRAN; 3 = GSM W/EGPRS; 4 = UTRAN W/HSDPA; 5 = UTRAN W/HSUPA; 6 = UTRAN W/HSDPA and HSUPA; 7 = E-UTRAN
